{"id":19656,"date":"2014-08-03T16:25:06","date_gmt":"2014-08-03T12:25:06","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=19656"},"modified":"2019-08-18T14:16:13","modified_gmt":"2019-08-18T10:16:13","slug":"istighfar-unless-you-stop-asking","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/08\/03\/istighfar-unless-you-stop-asking\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Istighfar: Allah forgives you unless you stop asking"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&#8216;Uqbah ibn &#8216;Amir reported: A man came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, one of us has committed a sin.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It will be written against him<\/strong>.\u201d The man said, \u201cThen he has sought forgiveness and repented.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>He will be forgiven and his repentance accepted<\/strong>.\u201d The man said, \u201cThen he returns to committing a sin.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It will be written against him<\/strong>.\u201d The man said, \u201cThen he has sought forgiveness and repented.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>He will be forgiven and his repentance accepted. Allah will not tire of forgiveness unless you are tired of asking.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 8918<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em> <\/strong>(authentic) according to Ibn Hajar<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u064